# Keywriter fork migration (active)

This session’s job is retiring the emergency patch script. Editor engine = **keywriter** (Qt 5 / C++ / QML). On-device binary = **Writerdeck**. Emergency layer = `third_party/keywriter/build-keywriter.sh`.

Handoff (read first): [docs/todo-handoff-keywriter-fork.md](docs/todo-handoff-keywriter-fork.md). Policy: [docs/decisions.md](docs/decisions.md) §3. Queue: [TODO.md](TODO.md) item 3. Archived general rules: [writerdeck-backup.mdc](writerdeck-backup.mdc).

## Drivers

- **This migration:** quality is the paramount driver. Prefer a smaller, correct slice over a fast, messy one. Stop if your own contribution looks low-quality.
- **Patterns:** before inventing editor behavior, check how similar editors do it (CodeMirror, Qt `TextEdit` / QScintilla, Mac/Linux text fields, etc.) and prefer proven methodology over one-off patches.
- **Whole project:** document integrity is the absolute paramount driver — the owner’s prose must survive as plain Markdown on disk. That outranks migration speed and harness cosmetics. See [docs/decisions.md](docs/decisions.md) § Document integrity, [docs/architecture.md](docs/architecture.md) § Document integrity, [docs/integrity-audit.md](docs/integrity-audit.md).

## Priority (non-negotiable)

1. Migrate **critical feature groups** into the fork first, in bulk chunks that belong together.
2. Do **not** first burn down leftover harness fails (14 non-critical). Touch a fail when its group is the group being moved.
3. Do **not** grow `build-keywriter.sh` with new behavior. New edits land in forked source once Phase 1 exists.
4. One migration slice per session (or one deploy cycle). Stop after ~20 minutes without sign-off for that slice; report and ask.

Suggested group order: (A) caret + shift selection + backspace/delete → (B) wrap / visual line → (C) undo → (D) combos / polish.

## Session shape

1. Read the handoff checklist; pick the next unchecked slice only.
2. Implement that slice only (Phase 1 pin, or one feature group into fork).
3. Verify on device for that slice (below). Update handoff checklist + [TODO.md](TODO.md).
4. Do not start the next slice in the same session unless the user asks.

## Verify (mandatory for the slice you shipped)

Deploy success ≠ tested.

- Writerdeck rebuild: `git push` → wait for CI → `bash scripts/fetch-keywriter-dist.sh` → `bash scripts/deploy-keywriter.sh -b` (never local `docker build` for Writerdeck).
- `journalctl -u writerdeck -n 30` — fail on QML parse errors or instant `editor process exited`.
- `bash scripts/test-edit-session.sh`
- After edit-behavior moves: `bash scripts/test-keyboard-harness.sh -t critical --fast` must stay **36/36**. Full `--fast` only when the slice claims broader coverage; update [docs/editor-testing/milestone-runs.md](docs/editor-testing/milestone-runs.md) after full runs.
- At most one Writerdeck binary deploy per session unless QML fails to launch.
- Do not run edit-session and keyboard harness in parallel.
- Do not `pkill -f /home/root/Writerdeck` (matches Writerdeck-server).

## Constraints (carry-over)

No jailbreak / Toltec; preserve OTA. Static Go for server: `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=arm GOARM=7`. Markdown on disk. Secrets: `secrets/remarkable.local.env` via `scripts/_env.sh`. Docs: terse Gruber prose; standing docs only (how → architecture, why → decisions, gotchas → lessons). Executable scripts: ASCII + LF.
